@startuml
!include _theme.puml
left to right direction

title Monitor — C4 Backend Component View
caption Level 3: key backend components inside the Spring Boot application

rectangle "Spring Boot Backend" {
  component "SseController\nGET /api/events/stream" as SseController
  component "EventBus\nSSE fan-out hub" as EventBus
  component "KafkaConsumerService\nCDC consumer" as KafkaConsumer
  component "PollingService\nHealth checks" as Polling
  component "EmailService\nAsync CRITICAL alerts" as EmailService
  component "MonitorMailProperties\nTyped mail config" as MailProps
  component "MonitorPollingTargetsProperties\nTyped polling config" as PollingProps
  component "JacksonConfig\nObjectMapper bean" as JacksonConfig
  component "SecurityConfig\nHTTP Basic + HSTS + CSP" as SecurityConfig
  component "CorsConfig\nOrigin whitelist" as CorsConfig
  component "RateLimitingFilter\nBucket4j per-IP limiting" as RateLimit
  component "SecurityAuditAspect\nAOP audit logging" as AuditAspect
  component "CriticalOutboxRepository\nOutbox persistence" as OutboxRepo
}

queue "Kafka topic\nlog-traza" as Kafka
cloud "SMTP / Groupwise" as SMTP
component "Frontend client\nEventSource" as Frontend

Frontend --> SseController : Subscribe to /api/events/stream
SseController --> EventBus : register emitter
EventBus --> Frontend : SSE comments + named events

Kafka --> KafkaConsumer : @KafkaListener consume()
KafkaConsumer --> EventBus : publish(DATA)
KafkaConsumer --> EmailService : sendCriticalAlert() when CRITICAL
KafkaConsumer --> JacksonConfig : uses ObjectMapper bean

Polling --> PollingProps : read monitored targets
Polling --> EventBus : publish(INFRASTRUCTURE)
Polling --> EmailService : sendCriticalAlert() when DOWN
EmailService --> MailProps : read sender / recipients / subject prefix
EmailService --> SMTP : send plain-text email
EmailService --> OutboxRepo : persist CRITICAL before delivery

SecurityConfig --> SseController : HTTP Basic auth per profile
CorsConfig --> SseController : CORS origin validation
RateLimit --> SseController : per-IP rate limiting
AuditAspect --> SseController : security audit logging

note right of EventBus
Responsibilities:
- hold active SseEmitters
- send :connected on subscription
- send periodic :heartbeat comments
- broadcast data/infrastructure domain events
end note
@enduml

